narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I developed a critical lens through which to examine texts
Exposure to some important thinkers, mostly women and women of color authors, and the race and gendered lens of their oppression.
I learned so much about how to structure and write a paper, how to read critically, and how to bring insights from books into the world.

I thought I knew how to right a paper before this class, but Professor Homans showed me what a true paper is meant to look like. I learned the importance of drafts and how to create an arguement. I actually enjoyed writing papers on the readings and improved.
I developed my discussion skills as well as my ability to analyze deep reading materials.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I really appreciated how the in-class discussions always felt very comfortable and open. I wish we got to some more concrete answers about the questions that we kept talking about through the semester but this also left me with more to think about outside of class and even now.

Strengths: the instructor! the books we read! the essay prompts! there were so many books by Indigenous authors, it was amazing. I do wish there were perhaps a bit more readings on queer topics but other than that, so good!
Ever reading allowed incredible conversation. Even when there was a reading the class didn't enjoy, we were able to speak about why we weren't engaged with the author's work.
I thought the course was done very well. I liked that our Professor asked/valued students' input. I also liked at the end of the semester how we started doing more small group work.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, I would recommend this course to another student because it exposes you to some important thinking from authors that we often don't hear about in canonical white and male-dominated literature.
I recommend this course not only for the literature, but for the professor herself. She truly helped me improve my writing as a whole.
absolutely! the readings are spectacular & professor homans is a gem!
